parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake actuator can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
loud chirping or grinding noise when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unpredictable braking performance can cause accidents or near-misses, especially when driving at high speeds or in emergency braking situations.
symptoms: The vehicle lurches forward when braking
the brakes do not engage immediately
the brakes slip or grab
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly when braking
the brake pedal feels spongy or soft
the vehicle takes longer to stop than expected.
